<br>
After having had a chat with Niv last night I am unsure if this is the correct path if I am ever going to cut it in RvR.  My pet isn't that much use in Realm combat and my AE Damage line (matter magic) would be much more useful.  Its not to late for me to change, but its going to make my life more difficult.<br>
<br>
If I continue on my current path, I can push my matter magic to 24 which gives me the second spell in my AE Damage without interrupting my Spirit Animation spec.<br>
<br>
If I decide to go the other way, I have to make up my mind before Spirit Animation hits 20.  This will give my all of my AE spells at the cost of my pet and my ability to solo effectively.<br>
<br>
If I was in an American time zone this choice would be easy, but considering that I spend 25% of my play time as the only guild member online it makes this decision much more difficult.<br>
<br>
My main concern about continuing on my current path is can we find a way to effectively use my pet in RvR combat?  As it stands, he can solo a yellow con mob without my help and I think that at higher levels might be able to act as a disposable shock troop, as long as we can get him outside the gates.<br>
<br>
Any thoughts or advice on this matter would be a help.<br>
<br>
Thanks<br>
<br>
Farmy <p><B><U>Farmelle VonFolger</B></U><BR>Cabalist of the 17th Circle - Palomides<BR><BR><B><U>Alienya VonFolger</B></U><BR>Mercenary of seven blades (430 Weaponsmith) - Palomides
